sgp4v
Class SatElset

java.lang.Object
  sgp4v.SatElset
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class SatElset
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class encapsulates the standard 2-line orbital element set for a satellite. Technical Description:
This class holds the satellite element set data. Checks are performed upon satellite initialization to verify that the input data in the the standard two-line element set format

SatElset

public SatElset(java.lang.String name,
                java.lang.String card1,
                java.lang.String card2)
         throws SatElsetException
This constructor takes the sat name and the two lines of the standard 2-line elset format as inputs. The ends of the cards are checked for additional columns containing average RCS and TOES values. Only the standard columns are preserved in card1 and card2. Then lengths of card1 and card2 are truncated or extended to 69 characters

Parameters:
name - the String containing the satellite name
card1 - the String containing line 1 of the elset (plus possible avgRCS value)
card2 - the String containing line 2 of the elset (plus possible TOES value)
Throws:
SatElsetException
